WELCOME, wild North-easter. Sharne it is to see Odes to every zephyr; Ne’er a verse to thee. Welcome, black North-easter! O'er the German foam5 O'er the Danish moorlands, From thy frozen home. Tired we are of summer, Tired of gaudy glare, Showers soit and steaming, Hot and breathless air. Tired of listless dreaming, Through the lazy day: Jovial wind of winter Turns us out to play! Sweep the goldcn rced-beds; Crisp the lazy dyke; Hunger into madness Every plunging pike. Fill the lake with wild-fow13 Fill the marsh with snipe; While on dreary moorlands Loncly curlew pipe. Through the black fir-forest Thunder harsh and dry, Shattering down the snow-flakes Off the eurdled sky.
